<p class="indent1" style="-uslm-lc:I12" xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">In the case of taxable years beginning after <date date="2006-12-31">December 31, 2006</date>, the Secretary shall adjust the $15,000 amount under paragraph (1)(B) at the same time and in the same manner as under section 415(d), except that the base period shall be the calendar quarter beginning <date date="2005-07-01">July 1, 2005</date>, and any increase under this paragraph which is not a multiple of $500 shall be rounded to the next lowest multiple of $500.</p>
